ing personal training session your spot will not be given to someone else unless you fail to schedule your sessions according to the guidelines listed above.</p>\r\n<p><strong>RESCHEDULING/CANCELLATIONS:</strong></p>\r\n<p>I value my clients and sincerely want what is best for you. I understand that sometimes life gets in the way of your best intentions. Your program will not be as successful as it could be if your attendance is sporadic and inconsistent. However, if you need to reschedule an appointment I will do my best to accommodate your request. If your request is made less than 24 hours prior to the appointment you will be charged a cancellation fee of ½ the session price. Canceling/rescheduling should be done via my website, sugoelitetraining.com. You will be notified once I have received your request to cancel/reschedule. In the event of an emergency or should you need to cancel last minute text or call my cell phone at 801.608.0658. However please be aware that excessive rescheduling/cancellations, regardless of the notice time, will be discussed with you and the fee structure will be adjusted accordingly. Failure to attend a scheduled appointment without notification will result in the session being forfeited and you will be charged at the applicable hourly rate.</p>\r\n<p><strong>LATE ARRIVALS:</strong></p>\r\n<p>Punctuality is important to the client and the trainer. If you arrive late the session will end at the pre-scheduled time. If the trainer arrives late the session will be extended by the time of late arrival.</p>\r\n<p><strong>SESSION LENGTH:</strong></p>\r\n<p>Personal Training sessions include one full-hour of training and/or discussion.\r\nGroup Training sessions include one full hour of training with 4-6 other team members.</p>\r\n<p><strong>CLIENT VACATION/ABSENCES:</strong></p>\r\n<p>Clients will provide two weeks’ notice for any absences and will reschedule all regular recurring personal training appointments that will be missed.</p>\r\n<p><strong>CLIENT ILLNESS:</strong></p>\r\n<p>If the client is sick or injured, the appointment should be rescheduled according to the rescheduling policy described above.</p>\r\n<p><strong>EXPIRATION DATES ON PACKAGES:</strong></p>\r\n<p>Personal training sessions expire 3 months from the date of purchase. Group training sessions expire 1 month from date of purchase.</p>\r\n<p><strong>PAYMENT:</strong></p>\r\n<p>Sessions are to be paid for at least 1 week in advance. However multiple sessions may be purchased at a time. For group sessions a minimum of 4 sessions per month must be purchased. I prefer payments to be made via my website and accept PayPal, credit or debit cards, however other methods of payment are acceptable if agreed upon before purchasing a session package.</p>\r\n<p class=\"text-center\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">L</span></strong>IABILITY <strong><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">R</span></strong>ELEASE AND <strong><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">I</span></strong>NDEMNITY <strong><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">A</span></strong>GREEMENT</p>\r\n<p><em>This Liability Release and Indemnity Agreement (this <strong>Agreement</strong>) contains release provisions that limit your right to recover damages in the event of death, bodily injury, or property damage to you or to others. It also sets forth certain obligations and requires you to assume various risks. Read it carefully before signing it.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>In consideration of and as a condition to my participating in the Activities, and in consideration of the services provided to me by</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>SUGO Elite Training</strong> <em>(Provider)</em>:</p>\r\n\r\nAs used in this Agreement: (a) Activities means any and all activities and services provided by, conducted by, or arranged by the Released Parties, including, without limitation, <strong>Personal Training, Group Training, Boot Camp, Boxing or similar Martial Arts, and other related Activities;</strong> (b)Released Part